Mesotibia (Fig. 11) moderately dilated and thickened, outer margin with two rows of sparse short denticles; setae of outer row well sclerotized, comparatively short; setae of median row shorter and sparser, covering most of posterior surface; 
posterior
mesotibial stria vaguely impressed, shortened apically; mesotibial spur stout, prominent and long; anterior face of mesotibia (Fig. 12) smooth; anterior mesotibial stria shortened apically; claws of last tarsomere bent, shortened, shorter than half its length.
